1
00:01:27,490 --> 00:01:35,000
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:37,930
[Episode 5]

3
00:01:40,950 --> 00:01:42,430
Why are you just standing there?

4
00:01:42,430 --> 00:01:43,530
Get to work!

5
00:01:43,710 --> 00:01:44,400
Go, go, go.

6
00:01:45,070 --> 00:01:46,330
Stop dilly-dallying.

7
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:50,170
What are you looking at?

8
00:01:55,870 --> 00:01:56,430
Move aside.

9
00:01:56,430 --> 00:01:57,350
Stop right there!

10
00:01:57,350 --> 00:01:58,400
Who allowed you in here?

11
00:01:58,400 --> 00:01:59,430
What are you doing?

12
00:01:59,430 --> 00:02:00,560
What are you measuring here?

13
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:01,490
Stop measuring!

14
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:02,870
Measure it properly for me.

15
00:02:02,870 --> 00:02:03,930
What are you doing?

16
00:02:04,230 --> 00:02:05,070
I have something to do here.

17
00:02:05,070 --> 00:02:06,200
I'll be back in a bit.

18
00:02:07,910 --> 00:02:09,210
Be gentle with it.

19
00:02:09,710 --> 00:02:10,310
It's done?

20
00:02:10,910 --> 00:02:11,910
We're measuring.

21
00:02:12,190 --> 00:02:12,650
Big Bro.

22
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:13,600
Hurry up.

23
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:15,680
Measure everything clearly.
Note it down carefully.

24
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:16,490
Write down

25
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:17,579
the size of each room,

26
00:02:17,579 --> 00:02:18,579
how many beds,

27
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:19,640
how many tables.

28
00:02:19,710 --> 00:02:20,240
Go on!

29
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:20,840
Okay, Sir.

30
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:21,440
Come down.

31
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:22,520
Who allowed you in here?

32
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:22,800
Get lost!

33
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:23,680
Let me tell you...

34
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:32,620
[Seasons Change Hotel]

35
00:02:24,180 --> 00:02:24,930
Gentlemen,

36
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,130
we have no grudge in the past

37
00:02:27,130 --> 00:02:28,260
and no hatred today.

38
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,079
I don't even know

39
00:02:30,079 --> 00:02:31,300
what kind of act you're putting on here

40
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:32,690
at my Seasons Change Hotel today.

41
00:02:32,690 --> 00:02:33,460
But whatever it is,

42
00:02:33,460 --> 00:02:34,920
we can talk it over calmly.

43
00:02:35,810 --> 00:02:36,530
In this world,

44
00:02:36,530 --> 00:02:38,790
there are no conflicts we can't resolve.

45
00:02:38,810 --> 00:02:40,590
Maybe it's all a misunderstanding.

46
00:02:40,590 --> 00:02:41,520
Don't you think?

47
00:02:41,970 --> 00:02:44,230
Are you the boss of Seasons Change Hotel?

48
00:02:44,690 --> 00:02:46,150
I, Little Northeasterner,

49
00:02:46,150 --> 00:02:47,130
mean it when I say something.

50
00:02:47,130 --> 00:02:47,660
Alright,

51
00:02:50,650 --> 00:02:52,180
my word carries weight too.

52
00:02:57,530 --> 00:03:00,180
If I finish speaking
and you still can't make the decision,

53
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:01,150
I'll make sure you end up

54
00:03:01,150 --> 00:03:01,970
drooling in your sleep in your next life.

55
00:03:01,970 --> 00:03:02,700
Understood?

56
00:03:04,630 --> 00:03:06,620
You're telling me I get to decide.

57
00:03:07,150 --> 00:03:08,680
So what exactly do you want?

58
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:10,970
I'm here to do business with you.

59
00:03:13,150 --> 00:03:14,550
I brought you customers.

60
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:15,660
Customers?

61
00:03:17,079 --> 00:03:17,500
Sure.

62
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:21,240
How many people?
And how many days are they staying?

63
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:21,900
I

64
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:23,030
just saw your

65
00:03:23,030 --> 00:03:23,810
basement.

66
00:03:24,550 --> 00:03:25,800
I can fill it up

67
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:26,460
completely

68
00:03:27,579 --> 00:03:28,800
and keep it full for a whole year.

69
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,530
How about that?

70
00:03:29,530 --> 00:03:30,740
Then where will we live?

71
00:03:30,740 --> 00:03:31,740
Shocked now, huh?

72
00:03:34,250 --> 00:03:35,310
You've seen it too.

73
00:03:35,410 --> 00:03:36,460
The basement

74
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:37,780
is mostly full now.

75
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:39,370
If it's full,

76
00:03:39,620 --> 00:03:40,280
no problem.

77
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,500
Kick them all out.

78
00:03:42,740 --> 00:03:43,680
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

79
00:03:43,710 --> 00:03:48,700
[Guest Room]

80
00:03:43,750 --> 00:03:44,550
Kick them out.

81
00:03:44,579 --> 00:03:45,380
Why should we?

82
00:03:48,530 --> 00:03:50,860
Let me hear how you plan
to educate people.

83
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:53,310
I'd like to hear how they educate people.

84
00:03:53,310 --> 00:03:54,440
What are you saying?

85
00:03:55,030 --> 00:03:55,760
Say it again!

86
00:03:55,860 --> 00:03:56,970
Didn't you understand what I said?

87
00:03:56,970 --> 00:03:58,210
-Where do you come from?
-Let's figure out the situation first.

88
00:03:58,210 --> 00:03:58,870
Okay, okay.

89
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,480
Talk to me. Keep talking.

90
00:04:05,250 --> 00:04:06,370
We're working on a project

91
00:04:06,370 --> 00:04:07,400
nearby,

92
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:10,200
and I need to find a place
for my guys to stay.

93
00:04:10,650 --> 00:04:11,240
I think

94
00:04:11,240 --> 00:04:12,700
your place is pretty good,

95
00:04:14,130 --> 00:04:15,590
so I want them to stay here.

96
00:04:16,540 --> 00:04:18,190
They're not here to
demolish the guesthouse.

97
00:04:18,190 --> 00:04:19,070
They're working on a project

98
00:04:19,070 --> 00:04:20,269
and want to stay here,

99
00:04:20,370 --> 00:04:21,430
not to tear it down.

100
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,320
But I'm really sorry.

101
00:04:24,270 --> 00:04:25,660
My guests are all regulars.

102
00:04:25,660 --> 00:04:26,540
I can't just kick them out

103
00:04:26,540 --> 00:04:28,270
-because of you.
-How dare you!

104
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:34,030
Don't think that your beard

105
00:04:34,180 --> 00:04:34,860
scares me.

106
00:04:35,260 --> 00:04:37,280
If you dare lay a finger on me today,

107
00:04:37,930 --> 00:04:39,460
I'll call my friend Tang

108
00:04:39,740 --> 00:04:40,930
at the police station

109
00:04:40,930 --> 00:04:41,740
and have him

110
00:04:41,740 --> 00:04:42,860
deal with you properly.

111
00:04:42,860 --> 00:04:43,500
Do you believe me?

112
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:44,700
I've got a bad temper!

113
00:04:53,810 --> 00:04:54,670
What happened?

114
00:04:55,540 --> 00:04:56,500
There's going to be a fight.

115
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:57,210
What? What?

116
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:58,390
My bad temper!

117
00:04:58,510 --> 00:05:00,110
You're asking for a beating!

118
00:05:01,070 --> 00:05:01,680
Enough.

119
00:05:02,780 --> 00:05:03,840
What are you doing?

120
00:05:05,330 --> 00:05:06,990
They can't really pluck them.

121
00:05:12,490 --> 00:05:14,660
You have relatives
at the police station, huh?

122
00:05:14,660 --> 00:05:16,720
If I didn't have someone watching my back,

123
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:18,720
would I dare do business in Beijing?

124
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:21,700
We pay to stay here too.

125
00:05:22,190 --> 00:05:23,870
We'll pay whatever they pay.

126
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:26,210
I'll even add extra for each room.

127
00:05:26,210 --> 00:05:27,070
How about that?

128
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:28,720
It's not about adding the money.

129
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:29,240
These people,

130
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,640
aren't ordinary guests.

131
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:33,380
They are like my brothers and sisters.

132
00:05:33,740 --> 00:05:34,560
I can't just

133
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:35,240
throw them out

134
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,430
for a bit more cash!

135
00:05:36,580 --> 00:05:38,040
No amount of money will do.

136
00:05:38,060 --> 00:05:38,930
Yeah, exactly.

137
00:05:39,420 --> 00:05:40,240
That won't do.

138
00:05:40,310 --> 00:05:42,500
Besides, how much more can you add?

139
00:05:44,180 --> 00:05:45,870
I'll add 20 yuan a day per room.

140
00:05:47,190 --> 00:05:47,920
How about it?

141
00:05:47,950 --> 00:05:48,440
Twenty.

142
00:05:48,470 --> 00:05:49,050
Twenty.

143
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:49,780
Twenty.

144
00:05:49,780 --> 00:05:50,780
Plus 20.

145
00:05:51,170 --> 00:05:51,750
How much?

146
00:05:52,130 --> 00:05:53,560
20 yuan a day per room.

147
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:58,470
One bed costs 6 yuan.

148
00:05:58,500 --> 00:05:59,600
He adds 20 yuan for a room.

149
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:02,130
That's several yuan more per bed
than before.

150
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,660
But I can't just

151
00:06:04,660 --> 00:06:05,740
kick everyone out at once.

152
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:06,350
Look.

153
00:06:06,420 --> 00:06:08,180
If you can't kick them all out at once,

154
00:06:08,180 --> 00:06:09,640
then kick them out slowly.

155
00:06:10,130 --> 00:06:10,860
If you do it quickly,

156
00:06:10,860 --> 00:06:12,270
I'll add another 10 yuan per room.

157
00:06:12,270 --> 00:06:13,070
Is that a deal?

158
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:13,890
Whether you make this money

159
00:06:13,890 --> 00:06:14,860
is up to you.

160
00:06:14,860 --> 00:06:15,680
Little Northeasterner.

161
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:16,300
Then where will we live?

162
00:06:16,300 --> 00:06:17,700
Little Northeasterner?

163
00:06:18,540 --> 00:06:19,630
Where are we supposed to live?

164
00:06:19,630 --> 00:06:21,030
Little Northeasterner.

165
00:06:22,450 --> 00:06:23,440
Wait, wait.

166
00:06:25,430 --> 00:06:27,360
If it really doesn't work,
I'll talk to them.

167
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:27,960
Talk to me!

168
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:28,630
Wait,

169
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:30,750
what are you even doing here?

170
00:06:30,750 --> 00:06:32,180
Is it your place to speak here?

171
00:06:32,180 --> 00:06:33,240
Are you the Big Bro?

172
00:06:33,390 --> 00:06:34,240
Are you blind?

173
00:06:34,770 --> 00:06:36,100
My Big Bro is right here.

174
00:06:38,420 --> 00:06:38,880
Big Bro.

175
00:06:39,540 --> 00:06:40,000
Hello.

176
00:06:40,330 --> 00:06:41,330
You've got style.

177
00:06:42,010 --> 00:06:43,100
Are you from Nancheng?

178
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:44,030
I'm from Xuanwu.

179
00:06:45,570 --> 00:06:46,370
What do you do?

180
00:06:46,659 --> 00:06:47,100
Me?

181
00:06:47,860 --> 00:06:48,870
I play the saxophone.

182
00:06:48,870 --> 00:06:49,600
An artist.

183
00:06:49,770 --> 00:06:51,830
More like the one being played by art.

184
00:06:54,810 --> 00:06:55,950
It's like this.

185
00:06:56,159 --> 00:06:58,140
I've been at Seasons Change Hotel

186
00:06:58,450 --> 00:06:59,850
for almost two years now.

187
00:07:00,330 --> 00:07:01,370
I heard

188
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:04,120
you're going to tear it down, right?

189
00:07:04,510 --> 00:07:04,950
No.

190
00:07:05,190 --> 00:07:06,010
They're just trying to

191
00:07:06,010 --> 00:07:06,870
kick everyone out.

192
00:07:06,870 --> 00:07:07,930
Kick everyone out?

193
00:07:09,540 --> 00:07:11,140
I treat this place like home,

194
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:12,480
and I treat the people here

195
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,480
like family.

196
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,360
Forget whether they agree or not—

197
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:16,300
I won't

198
00:07:16,630 --> 00:07:17,600
allow it.

199
00:07:18,130 --> 00:07:19,240
Right, Mrs. Wang?

200
00:07:19,370 --> 00:07:19,740
Yes!

201
00:07:19,770 --> 00:07:20,500
Right, Mr. Zhao?

202
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:21,060
Yes!

203
00:07:21,180 --> 00:07:22,250
Who's kicking us out?

204
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:22,580
Come.

205
00:07:23,740 --> 00:07:24,100
Fine.

206
00:07:24,770 --> 00:07:25,740
Saxophone player,

207
00:07:25,740 --> 00:07:26,770
you've got guts.

208
00:07:27,810 --> 00:07:29,010
I heard that clearly.

209
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:31,120
I'll count you in.

210
00:07:32,010 --> 00:07:32,620
So what?

211
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:34,450
Anyone else?

212
00:07:36,070 --> 00:07:37,190
Are we about to hear from

213
00:07:37,190 --> 00:07:38,790
your whole extended family?

214
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:40,750
Hello.

215
00:07:43,659 --> 00:07:45,190
Come. Come here, come here.

216
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:51,570
Next time you try to show off,

217
00:07:51,570 --> 00:07:53,630
get your facts straight first, okay?

218
00:07:56,220 --> 00:07:57,150
Nice to meet you.

219
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:01,250
From your hairstyle,

220
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:03,240
I'm guessing you're also in the arts?

221
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,040
I'm a painter.

222
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:07,020
Do you like paintings?

223
00:08:07,180 --> 00:08:08,440
If you like paintings,

224
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:09,480
I'll give you one.

225
00:08:09,690 --> 00:08:10,560
Once I become famous,

226
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:12,360
my paintings will be priceless.

227
00:08:19,830 --> 00:08:21,230
What are you laughing at?

228
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:22,370
My paintings are currently

229
00:08:22,370 --> 00:08:23,210
featured in a

230
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:24,680
huge art exhibition.

231
00:08:24,860 --> 00:08:25,480
I might just

232
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,940
become famous overnight.

233
00:08:28,950 --> 00:08:29,860
I get it.

234
00:08:30,980 --> 00:08:32,130
You're a fraud?

235
00:08:34,890 --> 00:08:35,240
Fine.

236
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:37,700
I'll count you in.

237
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:42,600
Does anyone else at Seasons Change Hotel

238
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:43,850
still want to speak?

239
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:53,280
Who?

240
00:08:55,370 --> 00:08:55,940
Zhuang.

241
00:09:02,130 --> 00:09:04,270
Here comes a little Mu Guiying.

242
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:05,600
You know Mu Guiying;

243
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,550
that means you're someone educated

244
00:09:07,550 --> 00:09:08,460
and polite.

245
00:09:09,220 --> 00:09:10,420
I don't deserve that.

246
00:09:12,100 --> 00:09:13,130
Anyone can stay

247
00:09:13,170 --> 00:09:14,480
at Seasons Change Hotel,

248
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:16,120
but we've got to be reasonable.

249
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:17,430
You can't just plant yourself here

250
00:09:17,430 --> 00:09:19,090
and act like you own the place.

251
00:09:19,770 --> 00:09:21,700
Are you saying I'm unreasonable?

252
00:09:29,870 --> 00:09:30,670
What do you do?

253
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,600
It doesn't matter what we do.

254
00:09:33,010 --> 00:09:34,460
As long as we pay the rent,

255
00:09:34,860 --> 00:09:35,620
there's no reason

256
00:09:35,620 --> 00:09:36,510
to kick us out.

257
00:09:36,670 --> 00:09:38,000
Zhuang Zhuang is right.

258
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:39,450
-Yes.
-You're right.

259
00:09:39,860 --> 00:09:41,250
That makes sense.

260
00:09:41,580 --> 00:09:42,640
Look at that girl's

261
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:44,500
sharp tongue.

262
00:09:45,550 --> 00:09:47,810
I always tell you guys to read more books,

263
00:09:48,250 --> 00:09:49,510
but none of you listen.

264
00:09:51,380 --> 00:09:52,150
Little girl,

265
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,720
you really can talk.

266
00:09:55,460 --> 00:09:55,990
Alright.

267
00:09:57,010 --> 00:09:57,890
I get it.

268
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:00,650
I'll count you in, too.

269
00:10:15,620 --> 00:10:17,420
Go ahead, laugh all you want.

270
00:10:17,670 --> 00:10:18,800
Big Bro, I was wrong.

271
00:10:26,940 --> 00:10:27,650
Speak!

272
00:10:28,690 --> 00:10:29,480
Go on!

273
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:40,530
Those guys are like bandits.

274
00:10:40,950 --> 00:10:42,150
They all have thick beards.

275
00:10:42,150 --> 00:10:43,350
They're terrifying.

276
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:45,170
What should I do?

277
00:10:45,750 --> 00:10:47,150
Tang, you have to help me.

278
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:48,680
Look.

279
00:10:48,910 --> 00:10:50,460
They want to stay in your place.

280
00:10:50,460 --> 00:10:52,320
Whether you let them or not is your call.

281
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:54,030
I said no, but they insist.

282
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:55,320
Does your big boss,

283
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:55,980
your uncle,

284
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:57,170
know about this?

285
00:10:59,210 --> 00:11:00,290
I haven't had time to tell him yet—

286
00:11:00,290 --> 00:11:01,910
that's why we called you here.

287
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:02,440
Alright.

288
00:11:02,910 --> 00:11:03,490
You

289
00:11:03,770 --> 00:11:04,550
should go discuss it

290
00:11:04,550 --> 00:11:05,350
with your boss

291
00:11:05,670 --> 00:11:06,410
and see whether this deal

292
00:11:06,410 --> 00:11:07,810
is going to be done or not.

293
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:08,500
Also,

294
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:09,720
regarding those people,

295
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:10,960
if they do anything

296
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:12,160
other than business,

297
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:14,270
call the station immediately.

298
00:11:14,270 --> 00:11:15,930
We will intervene right away.

299
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:18,010
Alright, that's it for now.

300
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:21,510
These guys are basically thugs—

301
00:11:21,510 --> 00:11:24,000
crude, vulgar,

302
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:25,840
completely unbearable.

303
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,270
I've been wanting to hit him
for a long time.

304
00:11:29,270 --> 00:11:31,060
I... I almost did too.

305
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:32,450
I held myself back,

306
00:11:33,150 --> 00:11:34,700
then I thought

307
00:11:34,910 --> 00:11:36,040
that wouldn't work.

308
00:11:36,510 --> 00:11:38,500
If we strike first,

309
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:40,430
they'll have leverage against us.

310
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:45,440
Didn't you pick up a brick today?

311
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,700
Why did you put it back?

312
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:47,950
I told you.

313
00:11:48,030 --> 00:11:50,530
If we strike first,
they'll have leverage against us.

314
00:11:50,530 --> 00:11:51,010
Zongbao,

315
00:11:51,010 --> 00:11:52,360
didn't you just go to the restroom?

316
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:52,940
Did you fall in?

317
00:11:52,940 --> 00:11:54,080
I didn't see you the whole time.

318
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:54,480
What?

319
00:11:55,030 --> 00:11:57,340
I was at the stairwell entrance.

320
00:11:57,550 --> 00:11:58,750
Those ladies

321
00:11:58,750 --> 00:11:59,840
were shaking with fear.

322
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:01,590
I was there comforting them.

323
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:02,940
Were you comforting them,

324
00:12:02,940 --> 00:12:03,510
or were you there

325
00:12:03,510 --> 00:12:04,840
shaking right along with them?

326
00:12:04,840 --> 00:12:05,120
I...

327
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:07,120
I even grabbed a mop.

328
00:12:07,150 --> 00:12:08,350
I was ready to charge.

329
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:10,400
For mopping floors?

330
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:11,550
Mopping.

331
00:12:12,390 --> 00:12:14,080
They've already pulled knives,

332
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:15,320
and we're all just people

333
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:17,440
living on the edge here anyway.

334
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:20,310
Are we really?

335
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:21,240
Who wasn't?

336
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,310
Who wasn't?

337
00:12:29,870 --> 00:12:30,930
Alright, alright.

338
00:12:31,550 --> 00:12:32,550
Say no more.

339
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:35,010
If they want us to move,

340
00:12:35,620 --> 00:12:36,750
then we move.

341
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:38,900
Tomorrow we'll quickly find a

342
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:39,890
cheaper place

343
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:42,630
and try to stay together.

344
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:44,480
You guys can look for a place if you want.

345
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:45,340
I'm not moving.

346
00:12:46,740 --> 00:12:48,000
That guy surnamed Feng

347
00:12:48,370 --> 00:12:49,630
is a ruthless one.

348
00:12:50,580 --> 00:12:53,260
A wise man knows when to yield.

349
00:12:56,290 --> 00:12:56,980
Tie,

350
00:12:57,030 --> 00:12:58,080
you can't treat my place

351
00:12:58,080 --> 00:12:59,210
like your workplace

352
00:12:59,630 --> 00:13:00,960
and show up on time every day.

353
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:02,630
Who can stand that?

354
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:06,340
Give us a chance to breathe,

355
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:07,270
let us...

356
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:08,340
Bro,

357
00:13:08,670 --> 00:13:09,370
I just took the brothers

358
00:13:09,370 --> 00:13:10,440
for another look around.

359
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:11,040
This place

360
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:12,460
is perfect for us to live in.

361
00:13:12,460 --> 00:13:14,320
The brothers are all super happy.

362
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:15,100
Do you like it?

363
00:13:15,100 --> 00:13:15,500
Yes.

364
00:13:15,530 --> 00:13:16,360
Then we'll stay here.

365
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:16,960
Stay here.

366
00:13:16,980 --> 00:13:18,790
You'll even get married here
and make it your wedding home.

367
00:13:18,790 --> 00:13:20,000
What exactly do you want

368
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,060
to do with my place?

369
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:22,300
Just stay here.

370
00:13:23,390 --> 00:13:25,290
There are so many shops

371
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:26,170
and guesthouses all around—

372
00:13:26,170 --> 00:13:27,750
why did you choose us?

373
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:28,130
What's so special

374
00:13:28,130 --> 00:13:29,480
about our place?

375
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:30,900
The location is good,

376
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:32,130
the size is right,

377
00:13:32,510 --> 00:13:33,370
and it's cheap.

378
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:34,590
That's low cost,

379
00:13:34,620 --> 00:13:35,350
high return.

380
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:37,160
Most importantly,

381
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:38,630
I like you.

382
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:39,460
Really.

383
00:13:40,380 --> 00:13:41,290
Don't be a coward.

384
00:13:41,290 --> 00:13:41,750
I just like you

385
00:13:41,750 --> 00:13:42,820
stiffening your neck like that.

386
00:13:42,820 --> 00:13:44,350
Come on. Stiffen your neck.

387
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:47,520
Tie,

388
00:13:48,270 --> 00:13:50,340
stop teasing me.

389
00:13:50,910 --> 00:13:51,310
You...

390
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:52,760
Just...

391
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:54,670
Let me off the hook, will you?

392
00:13:54,670 --> 00:13:55,800
Let you off the hook?

393
00:13:57,390 --> 00:13:59,180
I'd need to have a hook first.

394
00:14:04,220 --> 00:14:05,750
I'll tell you one more time.

395
00:14:06,580 --> 00:14:07,710
We are staying here.

396
00:14:08,410 --> 00:14:09,540
We are staying here!

397
00:14:10,580 --> 00:14:11,690
Do you understand?

398
00:14:14,010 --> 00:14:15,340
Stop talking nonsense.

399
00:14:17,870 --> 00:14:20,530
-Don't you scare when he acts like this?
-Come here.

400
00:14:20,530 --> 00:14:21,330
Go over there!

401
00:14:24,010 --> 00:14:25,410
Little Northeasterner,

402
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:27,440
let me tell you,

403
00:14:28,650 --> 00:14:30,250
I don't like to bully people.

404
00:14:31,050 --> 00:14:32,320
Seeing how aggrieved you look

405
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:33,450
makes my heart ache.

406
00:14:34,170 --> 00:14:34,630
Really.

407
00:14:35,650 --> 00:14:36,510
How about this?

408
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:38,050
Let bygones be bygones.

409
00:14:38,650 --> 00:14:39,620
From now on,

410
00:14:39,620 --> 00:14:41,000
I'll give you three days

411
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:42,430
to drive them away.

412
00:14:42,870 --> 00:14:43,530
Okay?

413
00:14:44,290 --> 00:14:46,520
How can I kick them out, Tie?

414
00:14:46,770 --> 00:14:48,250
They've already paid rent.

415
00:14:48,250 --> 00:14:49,410
They won't leave just because I say so.

416
00:14:49,410 --> 00:14:50,770
What can I do if they won't leave?

417
00:14:50,770 --> 00:14:51,500
Then do this.

418
00:14:51,770 --> 00:14:53,050
Call them all out.

419
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:54,740
If you can't handle it, I can.

420
00:14:54,740 --> 00:14:55,500
I'll talk to them.

421
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:55,940
Okay?

422
00:15:02,410 --> 00:15:04,140
Are you pulling a long face now?

423
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:04,960
Zhuang,

424
00:15:05,180 --> 00:15:06,370
take the brothers

425
00:15:06,580 --> 00:15:07,670
downstairs and round everyone up.

426
00:15:07,670 --> 00:15:08,530
See who is here

427
00:15:08,530 --> 00:15:09,360
and call them all over.

428
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,420
Then tell them

429
00:15:10,510 --> 00:15:11,510
Little Northeasterner

430
00:15:11,510 --> 00:15:12,810
is going to give them money.

431
00:15:12,810 --> 00:15:13,670
Okay, Brother.

432
00:15:14,370 --> 00:15:15,040
Come back.

433
00:15:16,870 --> 00:15:18,070
Go back and stay put.

434
00:15:22,740 --> 00:15:24,350
You just keep stalling here.

435
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,800
I have plenty of ways to kill you.

436
00:15:29,270 --> 00:15:30,800
Why are there so few people?

437
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:33,070
Why are there only a few people?

438
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:36,580
Everyone staying here is decent—

439
00:15:36,670 --> 00:15:38,330
they go to work during the day.

440
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:39,860
There aren't that many unemployed loafers

441
00:15:39,860 --> 00:15:40,550
or vagrants.

442
00:15:40,550 --> 00:15:41,840
Who are you talking about?

443
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:42,840
Did I mention you?

444
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:44,840
Don't assume I'm talking about you.

445
00:15:45,390 --> 00:15:46,400
Don't be afraid.

446
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:47,880
I've been here

447
00:15:48,390 --> 00:15:49,340
several times,

448
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:50,580
and you all know

449
00:15:51,030 --> 00:15:52,030
what I'm here for.

450
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:54,530
Today, I want to properly

451
00:15:54,530 --> 00:15:55,530
talk with you all.

452
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:56,120
Okay?

453
00:15:58,550 --> 00:15:59,480
Can you move out?

454
00:15:59,510 --> 00:16:00,270
Why should we?

455
00:16:00,270 --> 00:16:01,200
We've paid.

456
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:04,240
Then if Little Northeasterner

457
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,360
refunds your rent

458
00:16:05,390 --> 00:16:07,030
and gives you an extra half month's rent,

459
00:16:07,030 --> 00:16:07,830
will you move?

460
00:16:08,320 --> 00:16:09,480
Why should I pay an extra

461
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:10,540
half month's rent?

462
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:12,880
Okay. I... I'll move.

463
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:16,920
Thank you.

464
00:16:18,550 --> 00:16:19,680
What about you, Sir?

465
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:21,920
I'll move. I'll move.

466
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:23,960
Thank you.

467
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:27,040
What about you, miss?

468
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:27,720
I'll move.

469
00:16:27,860 --> 00:16:28,990
I'll move tomorrow.

470
00:16:29,730 --> 00:16:31,370
I'll go back and pack in a bit.

471
00:16:33,050 --> 00:16:33,480
Move.

472
00:16:33,830 --> 00:16:34,940
I'll move right away.

473
00:16:34,940 --> 00:16:36,160
I'll move tomorrow.

474
00:16:37,630 --> 00:16:38,430
It's settled.

475
00:16:39,720 --> 00:16:40,780
See? It's settled.

476
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:41,970
Talk to them nicely.

477
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:44,910
Go back with them

478
00:16:44,910 --> 00:16:46,310
and pack up their things.

479
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:47,950
Thank you.

480
00:16:48,030 --> 00:16:48,840
-Okay, brother.
-Thank you.

481
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:49,460
Let's go.

482
00:16:49,460 --> 00:16:50,320
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

483
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:50,640
Go!

484
00:16:50,660 --> 00:16:51,860
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

485
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:56,540
You...

486
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:58,390
You should talk to those artsy,

487
00:16:58,390 --> 00:16:59,000
talkative ones

488
00:16:59,000 --> 00:16:59,930
the same way too,

489
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:00,730
alright?

490
00:17:02,790 --> 00:17:05,250
If it still doesn't work out,
come back to me.

491
00:17:05,550 --> 00:17:06,550
Keep your head up.

492
00:17:08,349 --> 00:17:09,660
That's how I like you.

493
00:17:19,010 --> 00:17:19,480
Uncle,

494
00:17:19,980 --> 00:17:21,109
let me fill your cup.

495
00:17:22,609 --> 00:17:23,829
Anyway, at Seasons Change Hotel,

496
00:17:23,829 --> 00:17:24,960
you're the big boss.

497
00:17:26,319 --> 00:17:27,980
I really have no other way now.

498
00:17:28,420 --> 00:17:29,820
Please tell me what to do.

499
00:17:30,250 --> 00:17:31,310
Is there a problem?

500
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:34,700
Didn't they already raise the room fee?

501
00:17:35,030 --> 00:17:36,080
Remember,

502
00:17:36,350 --> 00:17:38,550
we're running a business to make money.

503
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:41,180
An extra 20 per room per day—

504
00:17:41,290 --> 00:17:42,460
multiply that by a month,

505
00:17:42,460 --> 00:17:43,830
then a year. Do the math.

506
00:17:45,180 --> 00:17:46,970
That makes sense.

507
00:17:47,330 --> 00:17:48,770
But these regular guests—

508
00:17:48,770 --> 00:17:50,190
I brought them in one
by one from the train station

509
00:17:50,190 --> 00:17:50,980
and long-distance bus station

510
00:17:50,980 --> 00:17:52,570
myself.

511
00:17:52,810 --> 00:17:53,810
I've been maintaining these relationships
day after day,

512
00:17:53,810 --> 00:17:55,830
and that's how they became regulars.

513
00:17:55,830 --> 00:17:57,240
If I kick them all out like this,

514
00:17:57,240 --> 00:17:58,830
I just can't feel right about it.

515
00:17:58,830 --> 00:18:00,050
They'll be hurt too.

516
00:18:00,350 --> 00:18:00,830
So,

517
00:18:02,140 --> 00:18:04,000
you'd leave the money on the table

518
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:05,530
and make me sad instead?

519
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:06,980
You just

520
00:18:07,070 --> 00:18:08,360
go talk to everyone.

521
00:18:08,740 --> 00:18:10,850
Refund or compensate them however needed.

522
00:18:10,850 --> 00:18:11,570
Hurry up and clear the rooms

523
00:18:11,570 --> 00:18:12,570
for these guests.

524
00:18:13,180 --> 00:18:13,440
Look,

525
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:14,430
listen to me.

526
00:18:14,900 --> 00:18:17,230
I hired you as the manager

527
00:18:17,380 --> 00:18:19,750
to help me run the place and make money,

528
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:21,900
not to play the loyal brother

529
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:23,630
and get emotional with people.

530
00:18:26,420 --> 00:18:29,400
[Guest Room]

531
00:18:34,900 --> 00:18:37,050
Which bastard pulled the switch?

532
00:18:38,320 --> 00:18:39,110
It's so hot.

533
00:18:39,110 --> 00:18:39,960
This power cut...

534
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:41,560
I never said I wouldn't move.

535
00:18:42,850 --> 00:18:44,660
Little Northeasterner,
are you actually in charge or not?

536
00:18:44,660 --> 00:18:45,710
It's so hot.

537
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:51,770
Is there no end to this?

538
00:18:52,530 --> 00:18:53,570
No warning for the power outage,

539
00:18:53,570 --> 00:18:55,100
and now the water's cut too.

540
00:18:55,790 --> 00:18:57,420
I just put shampoo in my hair.

541
00:18:57,800 --> 00:18:58,640
Line up.

542
00:18:57,850 --> 00:18:58,780
[Seasons Change Hotel]

543
00:18:58,780 --> 00:19:03,020
[Emergency Water Supply]

544
00:18:59,530 --> 00:19:00,160
Make room.

545
00:19:00,570 --> 00:19:02,130
The neighborhood committee
sent water for everyone.

546
00:19:02,130 --> 00:19:02,730
Over here.

547
00:19:12,090 --> 00:19:13,130
Bring the booze.

548
00:19:14,590 --> 00:19:15,290
After tonight,

549
00:19:15,290 --> 00:19:17,600
we're moving to Seasons Change Hotel.

550
00:19:17,700 --> 00:19:18,270
Is that good?

551
00:19:18,270 --> 00:19:18,880
Good!

552
00:19:18,880 --> 00:19:20,390
I found a place for you.

553
00:19:20,530 --> 00:19:21,130
Bottom up!

554
00:19:21,510 --> 00:19:22,910
-CBottom up.
-Bottom up.

555
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:25,020
Mrs. Xu, Mrs. Wang,

556
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:26,790
are you leaving today too?

557
00:19:26,790 --> 00:19:28,050
Luo, here are the keys.

558
00:19:29,240 --> 00:19:29,770
Okay.

559
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:30,880
If you forgot anything,

560
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:31,920
just give me a call.

561
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:33,110
I'll mail it all to you.

562
00:19:33,110 --> 00:19:34,350
Luo, you stay safe too.

563
00:19:34,350 --> 00:19:35,070
Don't worry.

564
00:19:35,070 --> 00:19:36,670
They can't do anything to me.

565
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:37,290
Take care, sis.

566
00:19:37,290 --> 00:19:37,620
Okay.

567
00:19:38,740 --> 00:19:39,560
Bye.

568
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:44,160
Seasons Change Hotel will always be there.

569
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:44,810
Lei.

570
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:46,280
Thank you.

571
00:19:47,550 --> 00:19:48,530
Mr. Xu.

572
00:19:48,690 --> 00:19:50,070
Have you packed your things?

573
00:19:50,070 --> 00:19:51,940
[Guest Room]

574
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:51,410
What's the rush?

575
00:19:51,980 --> 00:19:53,340
You should be in a rush.

576
00:19:53,350 --> 00:20:02,670
[Guest Room]

577
00:19:55,580 --> 00:19:57,980
I've been thinking about something today.

578
00:19:58,690 --> 00:20:00,240
Do you really believe that guy Feng Tieyou

579
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:01,700
will actually pay the rent

580
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:02,650
he promised?

581
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:05,170
First of all,

582
00:20:06,180 --> 00:20:07,480
our place

583
00:20:07,510 --> 00:20:08,670
is decent,

584
00:20:09,030 --> 00:20:10,000
but it's not exactly

585
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,430
upscale.

586
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:13,100
With an extra 20 yuan a day,

587
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:15,610
he could get a proper double room.

588
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:17,200
Is he a sucker?

589
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:20,190
Second,

590
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:22,220
with such a big deal

591
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:24,110
and so many people involved,

592
00:20:24,110 --> 00:20:25,090
If I were you,

593
00:20:25,470 --> 00:20:26,960
I'd at least ask for a discount.

594
00:20:26,960 --> 00:20:28,810
Discount? I'll break their legs instead.

595
00:20:28,810 --> 00:20:29,450
Exactly.

596
00:20:30,460 --> 00:20:30,860
Third,

597
00:20:32,050 --> 00:20:34,380
if they can't get any advantage on rent,

598
00:20:35,290 --> 00:20:37,140
then they'll try to take advantage

599
00:20:37,140 --> 00:20:38,220
of the rooms instead, right?

600
00:20:38,220 --> 00:20:39,050
What do you mean?

601
00:20:39,050 --> 00:20:40,350
What do I mean?

602
00:20:40,420 --> 00:20:42,740
Upper bunks, lower bunks,
even sleeping on the floor.

603
00:20:42,740 --> 00:20:44,180
They're treating my place
like a sleeper train carriage.

604
00:20:44,180 --> 00:20:44,720
Anyway,

605
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:46,610
you need to be clear.

606
00:20:47,380 --> 00:20:49,750
No proof, no deal.

607
00:20:53,110 --> 00:20:54,240
See you around, Luo.

608
00:20:57,220 --> 00:20:58,200
Get the hell out of here!

609
00:20:58,200 --> 00:20:58,700
Chen Yan.

610
00:20:58,700 --> 00:20:59,640
Go back to where you came from.

611
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:00,880
Chen Yan, who wants your junk?

612
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:01,350
Take it back.

613
00:21:01,350 --> 00:21:02,610
Listen to me, Chen Yan.

614
00:21:03,110 --> 00:21:04,770
Go back to where you came from.

615
00:21:08,270 --> 00:21:08,800
Chen Yan.

616
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:09,560
Feng Tieyou

617
00:21:09,610 --> 00:21:10,920
really knows he was wrong this time.

618
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:12,180
Just see him, will you?

619
00:21:12,330 --> 00:21:13,250
Every day now,

620
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:14,730
he doesn't eat or sleep.

621
00:21:14,790 --> 00:21:15,850
If you keep this up,

622
00:21:15,850 --> 00:21:16,450
this guy is

623
00:21:16,550 --> 00:21:17,890
gonna kick the bucket.

624
00:21:18,010 --> 00:21:18,740
Shut up.

625
00:21:18,940 --> 00:21:19,820
Who is your sister-in-law?

626
00:21:19,820 --> 00:21:21,020
We divorced ages ago.

627
00:21:21,090 --> 00:21:21,630
That's great.

628
00:21:21,630 --> 00:21:22,980
That way he can make
a contribution to society.

629
00:21:22,980 --> 00:21:23,380
You...

630
00:21:25,350 --> 00:21:26,100
Xu.

631
00:21:26,960 --> 00:21:27,890
Sis, you're busy. Go ahead.

632
00:21:27,890 --> 00:21:28,620
I'm not busy.

633
00:21:28,660 --> 00:21:29,580
Come, let me see.

634
00:21:29,580 --> 00:21:30,940
What do you have in your hand?

635
00:21:30,940 --> 00:21:32,240
It's nothing. Just some dried clams.

636
00:21:32,240 --> 00:21:33,850
A specialty from my hometown.

637
00:21:33,850 --> 00:21:34,440
That's wonderful!

638
00:21:34,440 --> 00:21:35,770
I just love dried clams.

639
00:21:36,180 --> 00:21:37,030
I'm telling you,

640
00:21:37,030 --> 00:21:38,050
get the hell out of here.

641
00:21:38,050 --> 00:21:39,030
If I see you again,

642
00:21:39,030 --> 00:21:41,090
he will never see me in this lifetime.

643
00:21:41,330 --> 00:21:42,640
How is setting up the stall going?

644
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:42,980
Pretty good.

645
00:21:42,980 --> 00:21:44,480
That's why I came
specifically to thank you.

646
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:45,460
No need to be polite.

647
00:21:45,460 --> 00:21:46,720
Just let me know if you need anything.

648
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:47,320
Alright, go on.

649
00:21:47,320 --> 00:21:49,050
I'll get back to work then, Sis.

650
00:21:50,050 --> 00:21:50,510
So nice.

651
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:53,250
Get lost!

652
00:21:56,180 --> 00:21:58,090
Room rates 50% off?

653
00:21:56,350 --> 00:21:59,120
[Cash and payment method]

654
00:21:58,500 --> 00:21:58,960
Right.

655
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:00,430
No need to shout.

656
00:22:00,500 --> 00:22:01,670
I wrote it. I know.

657
00:22:05,350 --> 00:22:06,570
Didn't you say before

658
00:22:06,570 --> 00:22:08,570
that you'd pay extra for every room?

659
00:22:09,250 --> 00:22:09,880
Now you...

660
00:22:10,550 --> 00:22:11,570
I kicked everyone out,

661
00:22:11,570 --> 00:22:12,700
and now you want a discount?

662
00:22:12,700 --> 00:22:13,700
Did I say that?

663
00:22:14,090 --> 00:22:15,380
Bro, you did say that.

664
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:20,120
Do I keep my word?

665
00:22:20,220 --> 00:22:21,950
That depends on your mood, Bro.

666
00:22:25,900 --> 00:22:27,760
I'm in a really bad mood right now.

667
00:22:29,700 --> 00:22:31,300
I've booked the whole place.

668
00:22:31,740 --> 00:22:33,000
If I buy a truckload of cabbage,

669
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:34,730
shouldn't there be a discount?

670
00:22:35,850 --> 00:22:37,380
Just sign it already.

671
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:39,570
How many people are you planning

672
00:22:39,570 --> 00:22:40,570
to put in one room?

673
00:22:41,460 --> 00:22:42,500
I knew you kid

674
00:22:42,500 --> 00:22:43,590
had a sharp brain.

675
00:22:44,420 --> 00:22:45,610
I've booked the whole house.

676
00:22:45,610 --> 00:22:47,000
I can stuff as many people in as I want.

677
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:47,590
Right?

678
00:22:48,850 --> 00:22:49,860
Tie,

679
00:22:50,030 --> 00:22:51,590
you can't do this.

680
00:22:51,610 --> 00:22:53,060
Then how should I do it?

681
00:22:53,790 --> 00:22:54,460
If you do this,

682
00:22:54,460 --> 00:22:56,240
I definitely can't agree.

683
00:22:56,530 --> 00:22:57,530
Northeasterner,

684
00:22:58,500 --> 00:22:59,960
you just said it yourself.

685
00:23:01,240 --> 00:23:02,990
The money you lost

686
00:23:03,160 --> 00:23:04,330
from refunding the rooms,

687
00:23:04,330 --> 00:23:05,720
adds up to quite a lot, doesn't it?

688
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:06,330
Right?

689
00:23:06,740 --> 00:23:08,640
And your reputation for kicking out guests

690
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:09,770
has already spread.

691
00:23:09,850 --> 00:23:11,580
If I don't take over this place,

692
00:23:11,610 --> 00:23:12,440
will the people living here now

693
00:23:12,440 --> 00:23:13,260
feel at ease?

694
00:23:13,420 --> 00:23:14,590
They'll definitely look for a new place.

695
00:23:14,590 --> 00:23:15,270
Once they find a new place,

696
00:23:15,270 --> 00:23:16,210
they'll pack up and roll out.

697
00:23:16,210 --> 00:23:16,660
Right?

698
00:23:17,290 --> 00:23:17,900
When that happens,

699
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:20,030
the old ones leave and no new ones come.

700
00:23:20,350 --> 00:23:21,950
Whether it's a loss or a gain,

701
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:23,460
weigh it in your heart.

702
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:25,000
Isn't that right?

703
00:23:28,010 --> 00:23:28,750
You don't

704
00:23:29,810 --> 00:23:31,070
need to think about it.

705
00:23:31,500 --> 00:23:32,100
Just sign.

706
00:23:35,570 --> 00:23:36,570
This contract

707
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:38,410
is out of my hands.

708
00:23:42,140 --> 00:23:42,610
Didn't you say

709
00:23:42,610 --> 00:23:44,920
you were in charge of
Seasons Change Hotel?

710
00:23:44,920 --> 00:23:45,960
Are you playing me?

711
00:23:45,960 --> 00:23:47,240
I may be the manager,

712
00:23:48,140 --> 00:23:48,880
but this inn

713
00:23:49,110 --> 00:23:50,310
doesn't belong to me.

714
00:23:52,160 --> 00:23:53,760
I'm going to check the rooms.

715
00:23:54,720 --> 00:23:56,250
Are you trying to push your luck?

716
00:23:56,250 --> 00:23:57,250
You want to hit me?

717
00:23:57,270 --> 00:23:57,930
Fine.

718
00:23:58,310 --> 00:23:59,560
If you hit me today,

719
00:24:00,180 --> 00:24:01,570
then this becomes a police matter—

720
00:24:01,570 --> 00:24:02,290
and I'll be saved the trouble.

721
00:24:02,290 --> 00:24:03,250
Come on.

722
00:24:04,530 --> 00:24:05,010
Look,

723
00:24:05,010 --> 00:24:05,740
stop trying to scare me

724
00:24:05,740 --> 00:24:07,270
with that police relative.

725
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:09,240
Business

726
00:24:09,700 --> 00:24:11,100
is about mutual consent.

727
00:24:11,260 --> 00:24:12,070
If you weren't willing,

728
00:24:12,070 --> 00:24:13,730
would we have gotten this far?

729
00:24:17,590 --> 00:24:19,790
I'm afraid the longer you drag this out,

730
00:24:20,750 --> 00:24:21,990
the more you'll lose.

731
00:24:22,330 --> 00:24:22,970
Right?

732
00:24:24,050 --> 00:24:25,050
Hurry up and sign.

733
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:27,560
Call me when you're done.

734
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:42,290
♪ Where are you from? ♪

735
00:24:42,370 --> 00:24:43,030
Sis.

736
00:24:42,460 --> 00:24:44,180
♪ My... ♪

737
00:24:44,420 --> 00:24:45,400
Xu.

738
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:46,400
What brings you here?

739
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:47,770
How are things with you and Zhuang Zhuang?

740
00:24:47,770 --> 00:24:49,500
We're good. Everything's fine.

741
00:24:49,500 --> 00:24:51,010
I wanted to ask you something.

742
00:24:51,010 --> 00:24:51,850
Do you remember

743
00:24:51,850 --> 00:24:53,850
the dried clams I brought you last time?

744
00:24:53,850 --> 00:24:55,550
I was just about to ask you about that.

745
00:24:55,550 --> 00:24:56,700
Those dried clams were delicious.

746
00:24:56,700 --> 00:24:57,460
Do you have any more?

747
00:24:57,460 --> 00:24:58,200
Yes, I do.

748
00:24:58,240 --> 00:24:59,010
I'll bring some over later.

749
00:24:59,010 --> 00:24:59,510
Okay.

750
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:02,030
I wanted to ask…

751
00:25:02,190 --> 00:25:03,750
Was there a guy with a big beard that day?

752
00:25:03,750 --> 00:25:05,280
Is he someone you know, sis?

753
00:25:11,900 --> 00:25:12,630
No, he isn't.

754
00:25:18,090 --> 00:25:19,270
You're a grown man.

755
00:25:19,610 --> 00:25:21,090
You're snooping around now?

756
00:25:21,090 --> 00:25:23,110
Sis, I'm not snooping.

757
00:25:23,500 --> 00:25:24,360
It's like this.

758
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:25,270
A construction team came

759
00:25:25,270 --> 00:25:26,240
to the small hostel

760
00:25:26,240 --> 00:25:27,810
where Zhuang Zhuang and I stay.

761
00:25:27,810 --> 00:25:28,850
They insisted on staying there.

762
00:25:28,850 --> 00:25:29,850
They want to kick out

763
00:25:29,850 --> 00:25:30,960
all the previous guests.

764
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:32,400
It's totally unreasonable.

765
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:33,530
These past two days,

766
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:35,570
they cut off the water and power.

767
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:38,550
Many guests were afraid of trouble,

768
00:25:38,550 --> 00:25:39,700
so they already left.

769
00:25:39,700 --> 00:25:40,820
But I'm young.

770
00:25:41,220 --> 00:25:42,350
I just don't believe

771
00:25:42,530 --> 00:25:43,920
they can do anything to me.

772
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:45,450
We live in a society of laws.

773
00:25:46,050 --> 00:25:47,050
That bearded guy.

774
00:25:47,050 --> 00:25:47,700
That bearded guy

775
00:25:47,700 --> 00:25:49,500
is with the construction team too.

776
00:25:49,500 --> 00:25:50,660
I was wondering if you

777
00:25:50,660 --> 00:25:51,510
knew him,

778
00:25:51,510 --> 00:25:52,240
could you...

779
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:53,930
could you put in a good word?

780
00:25:55,850 --> 00:25:56,440
Xu.

781
00:25:57,640 --> 00:25:58,500
Let me tell you.

782
00:25:59,590 --> 00:26:00,260
About this,

783
00:26:01,110 --> 00:26:02,510
they really went too far.

784
00:26:03,960 --> 00:26:04,650
I know.

785
00:26:05,090 --> 00:26:07,460
It hasn't been easy
for you and Zhuang Zhuang.

786
00:26:07,460 --> 00:26:08,860
But I can't get involved.

787
00:26:09,960 --> 00:26:10,640
Besides,

788
00:26:11,530 --> 00:26:12,470
Beijing is huge.

789
00:26:14,420 --> 00:26:15,680
You can live anywhere.

790
00:26:17,220 --> 00:26:18,330
If you come here for business,

791
00:26:18,330 --> 00:26:19,530
we'll talk business.

792
00:26:20,290 --> 00:26:21,620
If you run into trouble,

793
00:26:21,940 --> 00:26:22,870
I'll still help.

794
00:26:24,330 --> 00:26:26,310
But if you insist on bringing him up,

795
00:26:26,310 --> 00:26:27,840
let's pretend we never met.

796
00:26:31,610 --> 00:26:35,330
♪ Like a butterfly ♪

797
00:26:35,850 --> 00:26:39,480
♪ Flying into my window ♪

798
00:26:40,960 --> 00:26:41,830
Take care.

799
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:44,380
Luo.

800
00:26:45,330 --> 00:26:46,290
Here's your key.

801
00:26:50,810 --> 00:26:52,020
Call me when you get there.

802
00:26:52,020 --> 00:26:52,590
Will do.

803
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:56,060
[The rights and obligations
of both parties]

804
00:26:54,070 --> 00:26:55,620
Let's not be strangers.

805
00:27:01,940 --> 00:27:02,740
Mr. Xu.

806
00:27:04,140 --> 00:27:05,680
How did you know

807
00:27:05,750 --> 00:27:07,210
they'd try to underpay me?

808
00:27:07,410 --> 00:27:07,910
And...

809
00:27:08,640 --> 00:27:09,810
How did you guess

810
00:27:09,830 --> 00:27:10,610
they'd make people sleep in

811
00:27:10,610 --> 00:27:11,280
bunk beds?

812
00:27:13,850 --> 00:27:15,670
Whichever character you write,

813
00:27:15,790 --> 00:27:17,750
you have to play that role.

814
00:27:18,500 --> 00:27:19,270
You have to follow

815
00:27:19,270 --> 00:27:20,600
that character's logic

816
00:27:20,740 --> 00:27:22,140
to think things through.

817
00:27:22,720 --> 00:27:23,660
This is called

818
00:27:24,070 --> 00:27:25,930
putting yourself in their shoes.

819
00:27:27,980 --> 00:27:29,640
I really underestimated you.

820
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:32,470
Fine.

821
00:27:34,900 --> 00:27:36,760
I'm definitely not signing this.

822
00:27:37,310 --> 00:27:38,900
I'd like to see what he can do to me.

823
00:27:38,900 --> 00:27:39,910
If he dares to touch me,

824
00:27:39,320 --> 00:27:41,780
[Guest Room]

825
00:27:40,380 --> 00:27:40,980
I'll get Tang

826
00:27:40,980 --> 00:27:41,880
to handcuff them.

827
00:27:41,880 --> 00:27:42,960
Fine.

828
00:27:43,770 --> 00:27:45,810
Then you've got a feud on your hands.

829
00:27:45,830 --> 00:27:48,370
They have plenty of ways to mess with you.

830
00:27:48,940 --> 00:27:50,140
Then what should I do?

831
00:27:50,380 --> 00:27:51,240
I know it's a trap.

832
00:27:51,240 --> 00:27:52,840
Am I supposed to just jump in?

833
00:27:52,980 --> 00:27:54,840
I might actually have a solution.

834
00:27:55,660 --> 00:27:56,590
What's the plan?

835
00:27:59,500 --> 00:28:00,810
Little Northeasterner.

836
00:28:00,810 --> 00:28:05,510
[Guest Room]

837
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:02,660
Mr. Tao.

838
00:28:02,690 --> 00:28:04,030
I've got a plan

839
00:28:04,750 --> 00:28:06,410
for the Seasons Change Hotel.

840
00:28:10,850 --> 00:28:11,560
What plan?

841
00:28:12,290 --> 00:28:13,550
I know that because of

842
00:28:13,550 --> 00:28:14,740
the contract,

843
00:28:14,790 --> 00:28:16,050
you're in a tough spot.

844
00:28:16,050 --> 00:28:17,200
Leave it to Room 108.

845
00:28:17,460 --> 00:28:18,270
But Room 108

846
00:28:18,470 --> 00:28:19,930
has nothing to do with him.

847
00:28:22,250 --> 00:28:23,850
Stop keeping me in suspense.

848
00:28:23,850 --> 00:28:25,270
What is it? Tell me.

849
00:28:25,270 --> 00:28:26,220
I'm dying to know.

850
00:28:26,220 --> 00:28:28,030
Do you know why Guo didn’t show up

851
00:28:28,030 --> 00:28:28,970
when that Feng

852
00:28:29,590 --> 00:28:31,010
came over?

853
00:28:32,110 --> 00:28:32,740
Why?

854
00:28:33,750 --> 00:28:34,950
Let's step aside.

855
00:28:35,270 --> 00:28:36,420
Walls have ears.

856
00:28:36,720 --> 00:28:38,310
What's the plan? Just tell me.

857
00:28:36,860 --> 00:28:41,810
[Guest Room]

858
00:28:38,550 --> 00:28:40,920
Let's talk inside. Walls have ears.

859
00:28:43,110 --> 00:28:44,510
Section Chief Wang should be on his way.

860
00:28:44,510 --> 00:28:45,070
Today,

861
00:28:45,070 --> 00:28:46,510
he has a very important meeting.

862
00:28:46,510 --> 00:28:47,310
He mentioned earlier

863
00:28:47,310 --> 00:28:48,940
that he might be a little late today.

864
00:28:48,940 --> 00:28:50,460
So is he coming or not?

865
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:51,350
He is.

866
00:28:51,810 --> 00:28:53,470
He's a leader. Just wait a bit.

867
00:28:53,920 --> 00:28:55,270
This dump of yours

868
00:28:55,980 --> 00:28:57,310
is actually hosting a big shot?

869
00:28:57,310 --> 00:28:58,030
Tie,

870
00:28:58,220 --> 00:28:59,690
this isn't just some dump.

871
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:01,240
Not just any hostel

872
00:29:01,240 --> 00:29:02,990
can open in this area.

873
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:04,640
Luogu Hutong.

874
00:29:05,460 --> 00:29:06,590
This Section Chief Wang

875
00:29:06,590 --> 00:29:08,740
grew up playing with my dad.

876
00:29:08,740 --> 00:29:10,580
My dad helped him get where he is.

877
00:29:10,850 --> 00:29:11,710
Technically,

878
00:29:12,090 --> 00:29:13,690
I should call him Uncle Wang.

879
